headline: Boot Barn Holdings to Post Q4 Earnings: What Investors Need to Know
summary: Boot Barn is gearing up for a strong Q4, backed by store expansion, strong consumer demand and rising margins, setting the stage for higher revenues and EPS.

headline: Five Below (FIVE) Risks Market Expansion in a Cautious Retail Climate
summary: Specialty value retailer Five Below (FIVE) wants to expand its footprint while its competitors are backing off. The retailer intends to open 150 new stores in the current financial year. Recently, Five Below upped the ante in its first quarter and now expects to open 55 new stores compared to a prior guidance of 50. headline: 3 Profitable Stocks with Questionable Fundamentals
summary: Not all profitable companies are built to last - some rely on outdated models or unsustainable advantages. Just because a business is in the green today doesn’t mean it will thrive tomorrow.
